  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version 1.7.1`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nJSONRPC request `personal_unlockAccount('0xaccount', 'secret', '0x100')`\r\nwill unlock account '0xaccount'.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nI receive following error\r\n\r\n```\r\n(-32602, 'invalid argument 2: json: cannot unmarshal string into Go value of type uint64')\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to [wiki](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#hex-value-encoding) I thought that last parameter should be treated as `QUANTITY` and encoded as hex. It worked in some previous versions and it works in parity. IMO this should be at least described in wiki & standardized, so that we could safely switch between `geth` and `parity` if we use the same api subsets. \r\n",
